#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.5:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The First Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn11.5:0.3"
msgid "5. Subhāsitajayasutta "
msgstr "5. Victory by Good Speech "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.223, pts2ed1.480, sc1
msgctxt "sn11.5:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:1.2"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi. "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, a battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Vepacitti, lord of demons, said to Sakka, lord of gods, "

msgctxt "sn11.5:1.4"
msgid "‘hotu, devānaminda, subhāsitena jayo’ti. "
msgstr "‘Lord of gods, let there be victory by fine words!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:1.5"
msgid "‘Hotu, vepacitti, subhāsitena jayo’ti. "
msgstr "‘Vepacitti, let there be victory by fine words!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, devā ca asurā ca pārisajje ṭhapesuṃ: "
msgstr "Then the gods and the demons appointed a panel of judges, saying, "

msgctxt "sn11.5:1.7"
msgid "‘ime no subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ ājānissantī’ti. "
msgstr "‘These will understand our good and bad statements.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Vepacitti, lord of demons, said to Sakka, lord of gods, "

msgctxt "sn11.5:1.9"
msgid "‘bhaṇa, devānaminda, gāthan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Lord of gods, recite a verse!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:1.10"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Sakka said to him, "

# NOTE: A backhanded compliment?
msgctxt "sn11.5:1.11"
msgid "‘tumhe khvettha, vepacitti, pubbadevā. "
msgstr "‘Vepacitti, you are the elder god here. "

msgctxt "sn11.5:1.12"
msgid "Bhaṇa, vepacitti, gāthan’ti. "
msgstr "Recite a verse.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:1.13"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "So Vepacitti recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn11.5:2.1"
msgid "‘Bhiyyo bālā pabhijjeyyuṃ, "
msgstr "‘Fools would vent even more "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:2.2"
msgid "no cassa paṭisedhako; "
msgstr "if there’s no-one to put a stop to them. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:2.3"
msgid "Tasmā bhusena daṇḍena, "
msgstr "So an intelligent person should stop "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:2.4"
msgid "dhīro bālaṃ nisedhaye’ti. "
msgstr "a fool with forceful punishment.’ "

# NOTE: This suggests that anumodati meant something more exuberant than just “rejoicing”.
#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn11.5:3.1"
msgid "Bhāsitāya kho pana, bhikkhave, vepacittinā asurindena gāthāya asurā anumodiṃsu, devā tuṇhī ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "The demons applauded Vepacitti’s verse, while the gods remained silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Vepacitti said to Sakka, "

msgctxt "sn11.5:3.3"
msgid "‘bhaṇa, devānaminda, gāthan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Lord of gods, recite a verse!’ "

msgctxt "sn11.5:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "So Sakka recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.481, sc4
msgctxt "sn11.5:4.1"
msgid "‘Etadeva ahaṃ maññe, "
msgstr "‘I think that this is the only way "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:4.2"
msgid "bālassa paṭisedhanaṃ; "
msgstr "to put a stop to a fool, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:4.3"
msgid "Paraṃ saṅkupitaṃ ñatvā, "
msgstr "when you know that the other is upset, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:4.4"
msgid "yo sato upasammatī’ti. "
msgstr "be mindful and stay calm.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn11.5:5.1"
msgid "Bhāsitāya kho pana, bhikkhave, sakkena devānamindena gāthāya, devā anumodiṃsu, asurā tuṇhī ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "The gods applauded Sakka’s verse, while the demons remained silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:5.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Sakka said to Vepacitti, "

msgctxt "sn11.5:5.3"
msgid "‘bhaṇa, vepacitti, gāthan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Vepacitti, recite a verse!’ "

msgctxt "sn11.5:5.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "So Vepacitti recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn11.5:6.1"
msgid "‘Etadeva titikkhāya, "
msgstr "‘I see this fault, Vāsava, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:6.2"
msgid "vajjaṃ passāmi vāsava; "
msgstr "in just being patient. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:6.3"
msgid "Yadā naṃ maññati bālo, "
msgstr "When a fool thinks, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:6.4"
msgid "bhayā myāyaṃ titikkhati; "
msgstr "“He puts up with me out of fear,” "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:6.5"
msgid "Ajjhāruhati dummedho, "
msgstr "the idiot will go after you even harder, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:6.6"
msgid "gova bhiyyo palāyinan’ti. "
msgstr "like a cow chasing someone who runs away.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn11.5:7.1"
msgid "Bhāsitāya kho pana, bhikkhave, vepacittinā asurindena gāthāya asurā anumodiṃsu, devā tuṇhī ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "The demons applauded Vepacitti’s verse, while the gods remained silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:7.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Vepacitti said to Sakka, "

msgctxt "sn11.5:7.3"
msgid "‘bhaṇa, devānaminda, gāthan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Lord of gods, recite a verse!’ "

msgctxt "sn11.5:7.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "So Sakka recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn11.5:8.1"
msgid "‘Kāmaṃ maññatu vā mā vā, "
msgstr "‘Let him think this if he wishes, or not—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:8.2"
msgid "bhayā myāyaṃ titikkhati; "
msgstr "“He puts up with me out of fear.” "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:8.3"
msgid "Sadatthaparamā atthā, "
msgstr "Of goals culminating in one’s own good, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:8.4"
msgid "khantyā bhiyyo na vijjati. "
msgstr "none better than patience is found. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.482, sc9
msgctxt "sn11.5:9.1"
msgid "Yo have balavā santo, "
msgstr "When a strong person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:9.2"
msgid "dubbalassa titikkhati; "
msgstr "puts up with a weakling, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:9.3"
msgid "Tamāhu paramaṃ khantiṃ, "
msgstr "they call that the ultimate patience, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:9.4"
msgid "niccaṃ khamati dubbalo. "
msgstr "for a weakling must always be patient. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn11.5:10.1"
msgid "Abalaṃ taṃ balaṃ āhu, "
msgstr "The strength of folly "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:10.2"
msgid "yassa bālabalaṃ balaṃ; "
msgstr "is really just weakness, they say. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:10.3"
msgid "Balassa dhammaguttassa, "
msgstr "But no-one can challenge a person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:10.4"
msgid "paṭivattā na vijjati. "
msgstr "who’s strong, guarded by the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn11.5:11.1"
msgid "Tasseva tena pāpiyo, "
msgstr "When you get angry at an angry person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:11.2"
msgid "yo kuddhaṃ paṭikujjhati; "
msgstr "you just make things worse for yourself. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:11.3"
msgid "Kuddhaṃ appaṭikujjhanto, "
msgstr "When you don’t get angry at an angry person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:11.4"
msgid "saṅgāmaṃ jeti dujjayaṃ. "
msgstr "you win a battle hard to win. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn11.5:12.1"
msgid "Ubhinnamatthaṃ carati, "
msgstr "When you know that the other is angry, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:12.2"
msgid "attano ca parassa ca; "
msgstr "you act for the good of both "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:12.3"
msgid "Paraṃ saṅkupitaṃ ñatvā, "
msgstr "yourself and the other "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:12.4"
msgid "yo sato upasammati. "
msgstr "if you’re mindful and stay calm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.224, sc13
msgctxt "sn11.5:13.1"
msgid "Ubhinnaṃ tikicchantānaṃ, "
msgstr "People unfamiliar with the teaching "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:13.2"
msgid "attano ca parassa ca; "
msgstr "consider one who heals both "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:13.3"
msgid "Janā maññanti bāloti, "
msgstr "oneself and the other "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.5:13.4"
msgid "ye dhammassa akovidā’ti. "
msgstr "to be a fool.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.483, sc14
msgctxt "sn11.5:14.1"
msgid "Bhāsitāsu kho pana, bhikkhave, sakkena devānamindena gāthāsu, devā anumodiṃsu, asurā tuṇhī ahesuṃ. "
msgstr "The gods applauded Sakka’s verses, while the demons remained silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:14.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, devānañca asurānañca pārisajjā etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then the panel of judges consisting of both gods and demons said this, "

msgctxt "sn11.5:14.3"
msgid "‘bhāsitā kho vepacittinā asurindena gāthāyo. "
msgstr "‘The verses spoken by Vepacitti "

msgctxt "sn11.5:14.4"
msgid "Tā ca kho sadaṇḍāvacarā sasatthāvacarā, iti bhaṇḍanaṃ iti viggaho iti kalaho. "
msgstr "evoke punishment and violence. That’s how you get arguments, quarrels, and disputes. "

#. VAR: Bhāsitā kho → bhāsitā kho pana (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn11.5:14.5"
msgid "Bhāsitā kho sakkena devānamindena gāthāyo. "
msgstr "The verses spoken by Sakka "

msgctxt "sn11.5:14.6"
msgid "Tā ca kho adaṇḍāvacarā asatthāvacarā, iti abhaṇḍanaṃ iti aviggaho iti akalaho. "
msgstr "don’t evoke punishment and violence. That’s how you stay free of arguments, quarrels, and disputes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:14.7"
msgid "Sakkassa devānamindassa subhāsitena jayo’ti. "
msgstr "Sakka, lord of gods, wins victory by fine words!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.5:14.8"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, sakkassa devānamindassa subhāsitena jayo ahosī”ti. "
msgstr "And that’s how Sakka came to win victory by fine words.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
